    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">842.24/256</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Presidents Special Assistant</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-16">August 16th,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The President referred to me your
                    letter dated August 6th<note n="1" xml:id="d344fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_656">p. 656</ref>.</note>
                    relative to the establishment of a Joint War Aid Committee—United States and
                    Canada.</p>
                <pb facs="0773" n="659" xml:id="pg_659"/>
                <p>The President agrees that Mr. J. D. Hickerson should be a member of the committee
                    and that duplicates of all records will be filed in the State Department.</p>
                <p>The American representatives will exercise care in making certain that all their
                    work is properly related to the Department.</p>
                <p>Cordially yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry Hopkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
